text: I think from the chef’s perspective it isn’t practical for a restaurant to make fried rice based on quantity of leftover rice from the day before. And since leftover rice is just more dried out cooked rice, the more logical solution for restaurant needs would be like you cited from the chef - to cook a batch with less water that is more suitable for making fried rice - so they can control the ingredient quantity for a popular dish.
